TI  - Dimension of plots for inventory of regenerating tree vegetation in a fragment of Atlantic Forest in Pernambuco, Brazil
T2  - SCIENTIA FORESTALIS
AB  - This study aims to assess the methods of relative efficiency of the sampling in the definition of the area and shape of plots in surveys of regenerating tree in a fragment of the Atlantic Forest in Pernambuco, Brazil. 40 plots were installed for each of the different dimensions analyzed. All individuals with height >= 1.0 meter and circumference at breast height (1.30m above of ground) < 15.0cm were cataloged, identified and measured. The sampling and floristic sufficiency, rarefaction curves, Jackknife estimates and the relative efficiency were calculated and plotted for the plots dimensions of 5m x 10m, 10m x 10m and 10m x 25m because they satisfied the sampling error criterion admissible. The sampling of regenerating tree vegetation indicated that the plot of 10m x 10m is the most efficient given the high sampling precision, high species richness and low sampling time.
